<!-- EDGE HUGGING -->
<div class="row">
  <h3>Edge-Hugging</h3>
  <p>
    The default padding in the <tt>image container</tt> creates visual space between the edge of the <tt>feature banner</tt>. This can be overridden using the following classes (which are composable):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><tt>abs-right</tt></li>
    <li><tt>abs-bottom</tt></li>
    <li><tt>abs-left</tt></li>
    <li><tt>abs-top</tt></li>
  </ul>
  <p>This visual treatment is required for cases in which the <tt>foreground image</tt> must appear to <em>emerge-from</em> or <em>intereact-with</em> the visual boundary layer of the <tt>feature banner</tt>.</p>
  <blockquote>DO NOT mix opposing directional classes (eg; <tt>-top</tt> and <tt>-bottom</tt>. The net effect is not predictable as it is last-rule wins and source ordering of style rules may change during compilation.</blockquote>
</div>

